\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator stated that the programme in terms of all the criteria to be assessed meets the minimum requirements for accreditation and recommended that the programme should be accredited with conditions.  \line \line The programme is to be offered in the distance mode.  The programme is in line with the institutional mission and aims to prepare candidates for entering the industry.  The documents outlining the modules do not provide content but focus more on outcomes and assessment criteria and strategies.  There is somewhat of a contradiction between the outcomes which are focused on the South African context\'2C but the textbooks are from abroad.  Overall the programme is well structured and will be able to produce graduates that are prepared to further their own studies and\'2For will be able to assist communication practitioners.  The WIL component simulates industry where peer learning is used as part of the learning strategy.  The application states that the programme will be offered on all sites of the IIE Varsity College brand\'2C though the programme will in fact be offered through the IIE Head Office and not Varsity College.  All the required policy and supporting documents were uploaded.\line \line The programme targets recent school leavers.  Admission requirements are aligned with statutory requirements.  The Institution uses a range of recruitment strategies\'2C though the application is not clear under which brand the programme will be marketed.  Provision is made for admission via RPL\'2C and not more of 10\'25 of the cohort will be admitted via RPL.  The Enrolment Plan provides for small a small class of between 25-30 students in 2020 growing to 46 students in 2023.  All RPL processes are well documented.  A bursary scheme is available for deserving students.  All the required policy and supporting documents were uploaded.\line \line The Institution is well established and has access to well-qualified staff members.  The Institution uses technology to allow staff members to collaborate across campuses.  A full list of staff members\'27 detail per site has been submitted.  The Programme Coordinator is well qualified and experienced.  The Institution promotes training and development of its academic staff members.  The work allocation and academic leadership structures are governed by a \'E2\'80\'9CStudent Services Academic Development\'22 document.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line It follows from the list of staff members submitted that they are well qualified and experienced\'2C meeting and in some cases exceeding minimum requirements.  Several lecturers have a publishing record.  Support staff members are sufficiently and appropriately qualified. The Institution has a full set of policies and mechanisms in place governing recruitment and employment of staff members.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line The teaching approach is activity based and grounded in the place of work activities\'2C taking students systematically through the material with regular learning activities.  Students are expected to actively participate in their own learning through regular on-line sessions where modules are offered in a structured manner.  The teaching and learning strategy is heavily dependent on technology to overcome the challenges of distance learning.  Use is made of a LMS where students can engage digitally with peers and lecturers.  A mentor is assigned to a small group of students for learning.  Tutoring sessions are recorded and can be accessed again by students.  The system allows for monitoring student progress and identifying at risk students.  Students are exposed to a range of teaching experiences.  Students are required to complete an orientation session to ensure that they are confident on the learning platform.  Students experiencing problems are firstly supported by the lecturer and after that by the Student Relations Manager.  Programme evaluation committees conduct programme reviews each semester.  Overall\'2C the Institution has a commendable system in place to promote distance teaching and learning.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line The Institution has a comprehensive document guiding assessment practice.  Mechanisms are in place for both internal and external moderation.  Staff competence for assessment is built through training\'2C mentorship\'2C moderation and a quality assurance process.  The policies and procedures to ensure the validity\'2C reliability and explicitness of assessment practices are adequate.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line Detailed information for each site have been provided and all distance education students have access to libraries and resources on all IIE sites.  All sites have library and technical staff members as well as the infrastructure required to offer the programme.  Students have access to an Online Library Tutorial and the LMS platform is the main gateway for students to access learning resources.  Qualified librarians are available on each site.  Students have unlimited access to more than 750 000 full-text online eBooks.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line The Institution has a sophisticated national computer network connecting all the sites.  Full submission of the administrative measures for each site has been uploaded.  Effective procedures exists for all administrative functions.  The number of administrative staff members per site is deemed adequate.  All the relevant supporting documents have been uploaded.  \line \line The criterion dealing with programmes offered through distance education is rated as MMS.  The rationale for offering the programme in distance mode is sound\'2C and the enrolment plan provided is realistic.  The use of the latest technologies to offer the programme in distance mode will ensure that distance students will receive equitable teaching and will have equitable opportunities for interaction with lecturers and peers.  The programme is deemed to be an excellent distance mode programme using the current distance education strategies that are available.  \line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited.\cell \pard 

